definitions.definition: Pertaining to hypostasis , especially with reference to hypostatic union .
Personal , or distinctly personal; relating to the divine hypostases, or substances.
Pertaining to hypostasis ; depending upon, or due to, deposition or setting.
examples: hypostatic congestion, due to setting of blood by gravitation

definitions.definition: Of a gene , affected by hypostasis .
